data-triple-N3.o: "Vichy France, officially the French State (Etat francais) was France during the regime of Marshal Philippe Petain, during World War II, from the German victory in the Battle of France (July 1940) to the Allied liberation in August 1944. Following the defeat in June 1940, President Albert Lebrun appointed Marshal Petain as Premier of France. After making peace with Germany, Petain and his government voted to reorganize the discredited Third Republic into an authoritarian regime."@en
